This paper deals with the performance comparison of two routing protocols in a home automation scenario. The protocols are designed for low-power and lossy networks, which are typically used in the Internet of Things (IoT) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves simulation and evaluation of the protocols, which suggests the possibility of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity and efficiency of the protocols, which may fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the security aspect of the protocols, which may suggest cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as a possible category.
